This species with a wide distributional pattern, so far has been reported from: India and Sri Lanka ( Hutchinson 1940 ,
Wroblewski 1972
), Thailand (
Wroblewski 1968
), Vietnam (
Wroblewski 1967
), West Malaysia ( Leong 1966 ), Indonesia ( Breddin 1905a , Lundblad 1933 , Nieser and Chen 1999 ), New Guinea and Solomon Islands ( Tinerella 2008 ), and introduced into Florida, U.S.A. ( Polhemus and Golia 2006 ). Nieser and Chen (1999) mentioned one male from Borneo: Kalimantan Timur in NHMW.
